(thirdQuint)Efficacy, Safety, and Immunogenicity of a Plant-Derived Quadrivalent Virus-Like Particles Influenza Vaccine in Adults.

 This randomized, observer-blind, placebo-controlled multicenter, Phase 3 study will be conducted at multiple sites.

 The composition of the Quadrivalent VLP Influenza Vaccine to be used in this study includes a mix of recombinant H1, H3, and two B hemagglutinin proteins expressed as VLPs for the 2017-2018 influenza virus strains.

 Approximately 10,000 healthy male and female subjects aged 18 to 64 years will be randomized in a 1:1 ratio into one of two parallel treatment groups, such that approximately 5,000 subjects will receive the Quadrivalent VLP Influenza Vaccine at a dose of 30 1/2g/strain and approximately 5,000 subjects will receive the placebo.

 Within the two treatment groups, subjects will be stratified by site and two age groups (18-49 years of age and 50-64 years of age in a 1:1 ratio).

 Subjects will participate in this study for approximately eight to ten months, during which a first visit will be scheduled on Day 0 for screening and vaccine administration.

